            "q1": "Is this really 100,000 lumens?",
            "a1": "<p>The manufacturer-stated max output is 100,000 lumens under ideal lab conditions. Real-world output is still dramatically brighter than any standard flashlight \u2014 enough to light an entire backyard or campsite. We're honest: no flashlight at this price point hits lab spec. What you get is the brightest practical beam in the mid-range category.</p>",
